H0.text: The capital city of Nunavut, Iqaluit lies on which large island. Baffin Island

H1.text: The capital city of Nunavut, Iqaluit lies on which large island. Ellesmere Island

H2.text: The capital city of Nunavut, Iqaluit lies on which large island. Victoria Island

H3.text: The capital city of Nunavut, Iqaluit lies on which large island. ᕿᑭᖅᑖᓗᒃ

A4.text: Iqaluit is located in the Everett Mountains, which rise from Koojesse Inlet, an inlet of Frobisher Bay, on the southeast part of Baffin Island.

A5.text: Iqaluit is located on the southeastern coast.

A6.text: Baffin Island is part of the Qikiqtaaluk Region.
